The paper discusses the development of an integrated system for analyzing sensor data from power-generating assets, which involves the use of anomaly detection algorithms and visualization tools. This work is highly relevant to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the development of algorithms for detecting anomalies in large datasets. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a scalable event ingestion framework, which is relevant to the field of computer engineering (cs.CE). The system also involves the use of sensors and monitoring systems, which are relevant to the field of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the development of a visualization tool, which is relevant to the field of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a database (OpenTSDB) for storing and analyzing sensor data, which is relevant to the field of databases (cs.DB).
